I can definitely see some parallels between Gustavus Adolphus and Frederick the Great. Both were military innovators who introduced important changes in tactics and organization. However, there were also some important differences between them. For example, Gustavus Adolphus was more focused on using combined arms tactics, while Frederick the Great was more concerned with discipline and efficiency. Additionally, Gustavus Adolphus was primarily a defensive strategist, while Frederick the Great was more aggressive and focused on territorial expansion. Overall, I would say that while there are some similarities between the two, they were also distinct in many ways.
